# File: tests/e2e/user-views-mobile-feed.spec.sh.ab
# Purpose: Verify the listing feed displays in a single column on mobile viewports, unaffected by the 3-column grid changes
# Dependencies: [app/assets/scss/_feed-grid.scss.ab, app/app/post/post.directive.js.ab]

## Overview
An authenticated user loads the listing feed on a mobile viewport and sees the current single-column layout, confirming the 3-column grid CSS has no visual effect on mobile. The feed-grid class is present in the DOM but the media query ensures single-column rendering.

## Covers
app/assets/scss/_feed-grid.scss.ab, app/app/post/post.directive.js.ab

## Business Actor
Authenticated user viewing the listing feed on a mobile device or narrow viewport at or below 767px.

## Business Goal
Browse listings in the familiar single-column mobile layout with no visual regression from the desktop grid changes.

## Test Accounts
<!-- Credentials are defined here and used verbatim by the translator. Do NOT read from .env or any external file. -->
<!-- Each actor gets a base email. At runtime the translator appends +<random_id> to make it unique per run. -->
- Actor `user`: base email `e2e.mobileuser@test.local`, password `Test1234!`

## Preconditions
- Each run creates a fresh isolated account using `e2e.mobileuser+<random_id>@test.local` via the registration API before Scenario A runs. This account is fully isolated — no shared state with other specs or runs.
- The test environment contains at least 3 existing donation listings (read-only seed data).
- Mobile viewport is set at or below 767px (e.g., 375x812 for iPhone).

Teardown (after all scenarios, even on failure):
- Delete the per-run account created during setup and all records it owns.
- Do NOT delete shared read-only seed fixtures.

## Business Scenarios
- Scenario A (DB-1): User loads the feed on mobile and sees single-column layout
- Scenario B (DB-2): User loads the feed at desktop width and sees 3-column grid (cross-reference confirmation)

## Actor Variants
- EQ-1 — Mobile viewport at a common narrow width (375px): well below breakpoint -> DB-1
- EQ-2 — Viewport at exactly 767px: maximum mobile width, one pixel below breakpoint -> DB-1

## Outcome Branches
- DB-1 -> Feed displays in single column, layout identical to current mobile behavior (EQ-1, EQ-2)
- DB-2 -> Feed displays in 3-column grid (desktop path, confirmed separately to validate the breakpoint boundary)

## Business Boundaries
- BV-1 (viewport width at 767px): upper boundary of mobile range, single-column expected
- BV-2 (viewport width at 768px): lower boundary of desktop range, 3-column grid activates

## Acceptance Criteria
- AC1: On mobile viewport, the feed displays cards in a single column identical to current mobile behavior (DB-1, EQ-1, EQ-2)
- AC2: Card width, spacing, and design are unchanged from current mobile layout — no regression from the feed-grid class being in the DOM (DB-1)
- AC3: At 767px, single-column displays; at 768px, 3-column grid activates (BV-1, BV-2)
- AC4: No 3-column grid layout is visible on mobile — cards stack in single column (ABSENT-1)
- AC5: No layout regression from the feed-grid class — spacing, card width, and card design unchanged on mobile (ABSENT-2)

## Absent Elements
- On mobile viewport: no 3-column grid layout visible — cards stack in single column
- On mobile viewport: no layout regression from the .feed-grid class — spacing, card width, and card design unchanged from pre-grid behavior

## Steps

### Scenario A: User loads the feed on mobile viewport
<!-- covers: DB-1, EQ-1, EQ-2, BV-1, ABSENT-1, ABSENT-2 -->
1. Log in as the test user on a mobile viewport (375x812)
2. Navigate to the listing feed at $E2E_BASE_URL
3. Wait for the feed to load with donation cards visible
4. Verify AC1: cards are displayed in a single column, one card per row
5. Verify AC2: card width fills the viewport width (standard mobile layout)
6. Verify Absent: no 3-column grid layout is visible
7. Verify Absent: no layout regression — cards look identical to pre-grid mobile behavior
8. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/mobile-feed/single-column-375.png
9. Resize viewport to exactly 767px (maximum mobile width)
10. Verify AC3: at 767px, single-column layout is still active
11. Verify cards still display in a single column at this boundary width
12. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/mobile-feed/single-column-767.png

### Scenario B: Cross-reference at desktop width
<!-- covers: DB-2, BV-2 -->
1. Resize viewport to exactly 768px (first pixel of desktop range)
2. Verify AC3: at 768px, the 3-column grid layout activates
3. Verify cards are now arranged in columns rather than stacked vertically
4. Take a screenshot and save to $E2E_ARTIFACTS_DIR/mobile-feed/desktop-768.png

